<div class='function'><span class='function_name'><a class='anchor' id='rating_scale.__init__'>rating_scale</a>.<b>__init__(form, nodes=5, click_accepts=False, orientation=u'horizontal', var=None, default=None)</b></span><div class='details'>
Constructor.<br />
<br />
<span class='keyword'>Arguments:</span>
<br />
<span class='variable'>form			</span> &rarr; 	The parent form.
<br />
<br />
<span class='keyword'>Keyword arguments:</span>
<br />
<span class='variable'>nodes			</span> &rarr; 	The number of nodes or a list of node identifiers (e.g., 
['yes', 'no', 'maybe']. If a list is passed the rating scale will have labels, otherwise it will just have boxes (default=5).<br />
<span class='variable'>click_accepts	</span> &rarr; 	Indicates whether the form should close when a value 
is selected (default=False).<br />
<span class='variable'>orientation		</span> &rarr; 	'horizontal' indicates a horizontally oriented
<br />
rating scale, 'vertical' indicates a vertically<br />
oriented rating scale. (default=u'horizontal')<br />
<span class='variable'>var				</span> &rarr; 	The name of the experimental variable that should be used to log 
the widget status. The value that is logged is the number of the node that was selected, with the first node being 0. If no nodes were selected, the value is 'None'. For more information about the use of response variables in forms, see the form documentation page.(default=None).<br />
<span class='variable'>default			</span> &rarr; 	The node that is selected by default, or None to 
select no node. The value corresponds to the node number, where 0 is the first node. (default=None)<br />
</div></div>
